
[1]crasis

   CRASIS, n. [Gr., to mix, to temper.]

   1. The temper or healthy constitution of the blood in an animal body;
   the temperament which forms a particular constitution of the blood.

   2. In grammar, a figure by which two different letters are contracted
   into one long letter or into a diphthong.
